    We’re on the SafeWake website, but this section is introducing our new subsection called SafeSnow. Keep it very Apple-style: clean, minimal, premium, lots of whitespace. The section above is black, so this section should start in black and smoothly fade down into white so it transitions nicely into the next section. Add a subtle snowfall in the background (tiny drifting snow, very light—just texture, not cheesy). In the center, put a small label ‘SAFE SNOW’, a bold headline like ‘SafeSnow is here’ or ‘New season 2025’, a short line saying our snowboard lineup is now available in the UAE for GCC riders / Ski Dubai, and one simple button like ‘Shop Snowboards’. Under that, add 2–3 short feature lines like ‘The right board, first try’, ‘First-session size swap’, ‘Free wax & setup’. That’s it—just a small brand-intro moment, no carousel yet, This is close, but the aesthetics need a full Apple-style polish pass. Right now the typography feels generic and the text hierarchy/spacing looks off, so it reads ‘janky’ instead of premium. Please redo the styling like Apple: use a clean system/SF-style font, tighter typography, and proper hierarchy. Make the eyebrow ‘SAFE SNOW’ small, letter-spaced, and subtle. Make the headline bold, crisp, and perfectly centered with generous whitespace. The body copy should be shorter and clearer, with better contrast (no muddy gray-on-gray). Suggested copy: ‘New season snowboards, boots & bindings — now in the UAE. Built for GCC riders & Ski Dubai.’ Then place ONE clean CTA right under it (pill button, premium, not floating at the bottom).
    
