    Lastly, replace the 3 lines at the bottom with cleaner feature bullets (better spacing): ‘The right board, first try.’ ‘First-session size swap.’ ‘Free wax & setup.’ Keep everything centered, balanced, and premium.”, Perfect — keep the typography and snowfall exactly like this. Now fix only the layout + background behavior:
    
    Section height is too tall. Don’t make it full screen / 100vh. This should be a compact ‘announcement’ band, not a hero that fills the whole phone. Set the section to size itself to the content, with something like top padding ~48–72px and bottom padding ~48–72px (responsive). No huge empty space above or below.
    
    Background fade must be simple and consistent: start fully black at the top, then smoothly fade down into pure white at the very bottom. Right now it looks like it fades out weird near the bottom — remove that extra “fade-out” feeling. Keep it as one clean vertical gradient: black → cool gray → white. The bottom should end in clean white, not wash out the content or look like it’s disappearing.
    
    Keep snowfall confined to the section and proportional: the snow overlay should still look great, but it should not force extra height. It should simply animate inside this smaller section.
    
